{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"Included with: <b> ἵλαος</b> <br /> [see. entry near the end], ον, <i>Epic dialect</i> and Lyric poetry (incl. Lyric poetry of Trag., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Eumenides” 1040, 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Coloneus” 1480, 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Thesmophoriazusae” 1148)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: irregular <i>genitive</i> ἱλάονος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “UPZ” 1.8 (4th c.BC)\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; <i>Attic dialect</i> and later <b>ἵλεως</b>, ων (also in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Herodas Mimographus 4.25 \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>], variant for{ἵλεον} in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 6.91), dual ἵλεω 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Euthydemus” 273e; _nominative_ _plural_ ἵλεῳ 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Coloneus” 44, 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Memorabilia” 1.1.9 (later ἵλεως\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] <i>indeclinable</i> as <i>nominative</i> <i>plural</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “SIG” 985.47 (Philadelphia, 2nd-1st c.BC)\">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>], as <i>accusative</i> <i>singular</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.2Mac.7.37, 10.26, as _genitive_ _sing._, [prev. work] 2.22); _neuter_ ἵλεα 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedo” 95a \">LXX+5th c.BC+</a>]: <b>ἵλεος</b>, ον, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 4.94, 6.91 (see. above); also Cretan dialect, “SIG” 527.92 (Dreros, 3rd c.BC), “GDI” 5039.26 (from Hierapytna), 5th c.AD(?): Hesychius Legal icographus \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <b>ἵληϝος</b>, uncertain in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “IG” 5(1).1562 (6th c.AD: Olympiodorus Philosophus, 6th-5th c.BC\">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>],= epigram cited in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Pausanias Periegeta 5.24.3, where ἱλάῳ)\">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]; <i>Aeolic dialect</i> <b>ἴλλαος</b> [<a href=\"javascript:vo